organic.title: Special Needs Shelters | Florida Department of Health
organic.snippet: Eligibility for Special Needs Shelters ... The capabilities of each special needs shelter vary based upon a community's needs and available resources. Contact your Emergency Management Office or visit the Florida Department of Health County Locations Directory for more information.

organic.title: SPECIAL NEEDS SHELTER | Fort Pierce, FL - Official Website
organic.snippet: The program is coordinated by the Division of Emergency Management and the St. Lucie Health Department and each application will be reviewed to verify qualification. Individuals may register themselves or a family member by visiting www.stlucieco.gov/eoc or by calling (772) 462-8100.

organic.title: Special Needs Shelter - Florida Department of Health in Pasco County
organic.snippet: Pasco County Special Needs Shelters. The Florida Department of Health in Pasco County has two special needs shelters: West Pasco Special Needs Shelter: Located at the Mike Fasano Regional Hurricane Shelter in Hudson. East Pasco Special Needs Shelter: Located at Wiregrass High School in Wesley Chapel.

organic.title: Special Needs | Sumter County, FL - Official Website
organic.snippet: You will be able to evacuate to the Special Needs Shelter at the Wildwood Community Center located at 6500 Powell Road, Wildwood, FL 34785.
